cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "workingclass — Laborer's Companion"
message: >-
  If you reference this work or build on top of it, please cite it as below.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "the workingclass-ai contributors"
    website: "https://github.com/workingclass-ai/workingclass"
repository-code: "https://github.com/workingclass-ai/workingclass"
url: "https://github.com/workingclass-ai/workingclass"
abstract: >-
  An agent skill that stands on the side of workers — a clarity tool for
  workplace rhetoric decoding, performance-review analysis, overtime
  decisions, stay-or-leave framing, salary negotiation, PIP survival, and
  job-search strategy. Operates as an installable skill across multiple
  agent platforms (Claude Code, Codex, Cursor) with full support for seven
  languages and a structured eval framework for cross-version regression
  detection.
keywords:
